snippet.textDisplay:
hm...nothing better  than Noori in the production...makes feel more comfortable with the absence of Rohail Hiatt´s Midas touch.
I love the ethnic influences and musicians...very talented. 
Extremely poppish but full of energy. Nice to listen the heavy fuzzy guitar by the hands of Ali perfect vocals..perfect techy scenarios...
Not that  I like only softer music from this country but when it comes to rock, they do it with class.
Something I appreciate in Pakistan songs is that they last more than average riving us to a longer fulfilment and joy. 
This performance ia not a piece of art of this season 9 or I haven´t been acustommed to this yet...let´s wait.
